This paper discusses the challenge of detecting malware that uses information-hiding techniques, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms to detect such malware, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the need for better software engineering practices to prevent malware attacks, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of data structures and algorithms to detect malware, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the use of network infrastructure to detect malware communication attempts, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
